👉 If keyring exists there → copy it


---

🔥 Step 3: Recreate keyring (if no backup)

Run:

sudo ceph-authtool --create-keyring /etc/ceph/ceph.client.admin.keyring \
--gen-key -n client.admin \
--cap mon 'allow *' \
--cap osd 'allow *' \
--cap mgr 'allow *'


---

🔥 Step 4: Fix permissions

sudo chown root:sys_protected /etc/ceph/ceph.client.admin.keyring
sudo chmod 640 /etc/ceph/ceph.client.admin.keyring


---

🔥 Step 5: Restart MON

sudo sm-restart service ceph-mon


---

